CreateJsonString

public java.lang.String CreateJsonString(int id,
                                         int transactionID,
                                         boolean isCredit,
                                         float amount,
                                         java.lang.String date,
                                         java.lang.String time,
                                         float balance,
                                         java.lang.String details)
It returns a JSON response that can be read by AJAX event handlers to decide whether request was successful or a failure

Parameters:
id - contains the count for each sub-entry in json packet
transactionID - contains the trasactionID of transactions
isCredit - is 1 if transaction is credit type
amount - contains the amount of transaction
date - contains the date of transaction
time - contains the time of transaction
balance - contains the balance of account
details - contains the description of transaction
Returns:
The JSON response in the format "{'success':true/false, 'size' : , 'data' : [{'id': 1,'tid':'','type':'credit/debit', 'amount':'','date':'','time':'','balance':''},{2nd record and so on}],'path':}"
